    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/2eea63f8400287f4.html':'<div>Tribal elders say the Taliban are far from defeated.\xa0 The Taliban continue to wage a brutal war, taking a toll on Afghan citizens and American forces.\xa0 The Department of Defense has identified 1,761 American service members who have died in the Afghan war and related operations as of Sept. 21, about 10 years since the start of the war. In visiting Afghanistan monthly in The Big Picture, we try to reflect our troops presence in the country as well as their interaction with the Afghan people.\xa0 -- <em>Paula Nelson</em> (<a href="http://www.boston.com/bigpicture/2011/09/afghanistan_september_2011.html">54 photos total</a>)</div><div><a name="photo1"></a><a href="http://www.boston.com/bigpicture/2011/09/afghanistan_september_2011.html"><img src="http://inapcache.boston.com/universal/site_graphics/blogs/bigpicture/afghan_sept2011/bp1.jpg" style="height:679px;width:990px"></a><br><div>US soldiers from the 27th Infantry Regiment fire 120-mm mortar rounds toward insurgent positions at Outpost Monti in Kunar province on Sept. 17. After a decade of fighting in Afghanistan, 130,000 troops from dozens of countries continue to battle resilient Taliban, who use homemade bombs and guerrilla tactics in a bid to undermine the Afghan government and the NATO mission. (Tauseef Mustafa/AFP/Getty Images) <div></div></div></div>\n<br style="clear:both">\n<br style="clear:both">\n  <a style="font-size:10px;color:maroon" href="http://www.pheedcontent.com/hostedMorselClick.php?hfmm=v3:4aedacb06cef7856a7be661fdadb354b:d%2ByK0AOt43gBJYkhMASV1gGDfvYuEQoa6z%2BvetO4VFqZymGnIOOFmZnMQjX7wL%2BXHABDQE4eVYcjZXE%3D"><img border="0" title="Add to Facebook" alt="Add to Facebook" src="http://images.pheedo.com/images/mm/facebook.gif"></a>\n  <a style="font-size:10px;color:maroon" href="http://www.pheedcontent.com/hostedMorselClick.php?hfmm=v3:a5efd7646a530ff2793e7d9cd62257ed:AYUaSoa0ADlBCAoYvXf3FevVpmIRj4GuxcbAzW0eEgxzFVn6c9x1l