tp://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/themes/weburbanist-3/images/feed-SU.png" width="74px" height="19px"></a>\n  <a style="margin-left:9px" href="http://twitter.com/home?status=%40weburbanist+http%3A%2F%2Fweburbanist.com%2F2011%2F09%2F19%2Fhorror-prisons-top-13-most-terrifying-fictional-facilities%2F+Horror+Prisons%3A+Top+13+Most+Terr"><img border="none" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/themes/weburbanist-3/images/feed-retweet.png" height="19" width="48"></a>\n  <a style="margin-left:5px" href="http://twitter.com/weburbanist"><img border="none" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/themes/weburbanist-3/images/feed-twitter.png" width="220px" height="19px"></a>\n<div style="clear:both"></div>\n\n    <hr width="375px" align="left">\n    <span style="float:left;margin-left:10px">[ By <a href="http://weburbanist.com/steph">Steph</a> in <a href="http://weburbanist.com/category/games/" title="View all posts in Games &amp; Gaming" rel="category tag">Games &amp; Gaming</a> &amp; <a href="http://weburbanist.com/category/urbanism/" title="View all posts in Urbanism" rel="category tag">Urbanism</a>. ]</span>\n\n<br><br>\n  <span style="color:#ddd;float:left;margin-left:10px">[ <a style="color:#ddd" href="http://weburbanist.com">WebUrbanist</a> | <a style="color:#ddd" href="http://weburbanist.com/archives">Archives</a> | <a style="color:#ddd" href="http://weburbanist.com/galleries">Galleries</a> | <a style="color:#ddd" href="http://weburbanist.com/privacy/">Privacy</a> | <a style="color:#ddd" href="http://weburbanist.com/terms/">TOS</a> ]</span>\n<div style="clear:both"></div>\n<br>\n\n \n<div style="clear:both"></div>\n<br>\n    \n    \n    <img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WebUrbanist/~4/Tv_ZnpijBuo" height="1" width="1">', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/01655a125bfd0b4e.html':'\n              \n    [ By <a href="http://weburbanist.com/steve">Steve</a> in <a href="http://weburbanist.com/category/urban-furniture/" title="View all posts in Furniture &amp; Interiors" rel="category tag">Furniture &amp; Interiors</a> &amp; <a href="http://weburbanist.com/category/geek-art/" title="View all posts in Gadgets &amp; Geek Art" rel="category tag">Gadgets &amp; Geek Art</a> &amp; <a href="http://weburbanist.com/category/uncategorized/" title="View all posts in Various Uncategorized" rel="category tag">Various Uncategorized</a>. ]\n    \n    <p><img title="pillows_main" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_main.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="427"><br>\n<a href="http://weburbanist.com/2010/10/04/sleeping-giants-12-sky-high-abandoned-buildings/">Sleeping</a> beauties they\u2019re not, and sweet dreams may be too much to expect from these 15 nightmarish pillow designs. Whether you\u2019re a certified head case or looking to become one, sooner or later everybody\u2019s head hits the pillow case. When your time comes, they\u2019ll be waiting.</p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<h4>Dinosaur Bone Pillow</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_1a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_1a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="516"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://www.ohgizmo.com/2009/02/24/giant-foam-dinosaur-bones-are-way-cooler-than-traditional-throw-pillows/">OhGizmo!</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Well ain\u2019t that a kick in the Cretaceous! Japanese designer <a href="http://www.sayakayamamoto.com/2008/design/living-with-dinosaurs/">Sayaka Yamamoto</a> has created \u201ca collection of soft interior objects inspired by dinosaur bones\u201d, though for what ultimate purpose? Inspired by bones they may be, but these ivory-hued pillows made from rubber-coated foam make osteoporosis sound good.</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_1b" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_1b.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="426"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(image via: <a href="http://playfast.exblog.jp/9813516/">Playfast</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Make no bones about it, Yamamoto\u2019s foamy fossils add a distinctive touch to one\u2019s home decor scheme. They\u2019re not recommended for dog-owners, though\u2026 you think Fido chews up the furniture now??</p>\n<h4>Pillowig: A Bed-Head To Go</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_2a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_2a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="497"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://itp.nyu.edu/~jyp243/jy/pillow.htm">Joo Youn Paek</a> and <a href="http://earthtodave.com/wp/page/6/">Earth To Dave</a>)</span></p>\n<p>It\u2019s no fun being a narcoleptic\u2026 <em>until now!</em> Korean artist and designer <a href="http://itp.nyu.edu/~jyp243/jy/pillow.htm">Joo Youn Paek</a> created the wearable Pillowig to, as he puts it, <em>\u201ccomfort tiredness of people in daily lives, enabling users to sleep comfortably whenever and whenever they\u2019d like.\u201d</em> Paek may have something here: out of 50 Pillowigs produced, he sold 47. Kinda gives a whole new meaning to the term, \u201cSleepyhead\u201d.</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_2b" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_2b.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="348"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(image via: <a href="http://itp.nyu.edu/~jyp243/jy/pillow.htm">Joo Youn Paek</a>)</span></p>\n<p>It takes a special kind of person to wear a Pillowig in public, but thankfully these kinds of people tend to congregate with one another and leave us regular folks alone.</p>\n<h4>Thighs &amp; Whispers Pillow</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_3a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_3a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="625"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://www.japannewbie.com/2006/01/06/hizamakura-china-version/">Japan Newbie</a>, <a href="http://theywonderwhy.blogspot.com/2008/01/sweet-dreams.html">And They Wonder Why</a> and <a href="http://blogs.laweekly.com/stylecouncil/2010/05/japanese_lap_pillow_so_bad_it.php">LA Weekly</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Available in red-skirt or black-skirt versions (plus red and blue \u201csilk\u201d for Chinese export), the Hizamakura knee lap pillow is the ideal comfort item for guys who are going through a particularly difficult break-up\u2026 and also for guys who\u2019ve never had the chance to experience a break-up in the first place.</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_3b" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_3b.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="351"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(image via: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/paxling/1050931760/">Paxling</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Just in case potential buyers are confused by the exact purpose of an imitation woman\u2019s torso, the Hizamakura knee lap pillow\u2019s packaging includes a helpful illustration of the suggested usage. Now I feel so much better.</p>\n<h4>Armed &amp; Fabulous Boyfriend Arm Pillow</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_4a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_4a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="745"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://www.activeforever.com/p-2131-the-boyfriend-arm-pillow.aspx">ActiveForever.com</a>)</span></p>\n<p>What\u2019s good for the gander is good for the goose, as the Boyfriend Arm Pillow so succinctly demonstrates. This item strips away all the extraneous attributes gals don\u2019t need in a guy, especially if all they want is some sleep. The Boyfriend Arm Pillow is being sold at <a href="http://www.activeforever.com/p-2131-the-boyfriend-arm-pillow.aspx">ActiveForever.com</a>, a site specializing in <em>\u201cMedical Supplies, Safety Equipment &amp; Innovative Health Products.\u201d</em> Not like those pervy Lap Pillows at all, amiright?</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_4b" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_4b.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="670"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-512410/Alone-Valentines-Women-offered-boyfriend-arm-pillow-hug-night.html">DailyMail UK</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Looking like Two &amp; a Half Men minus the two men, the Boyfriend Arm Pillow reeks of crass exploitation\u2026 or, it just needs a wash.</p>\n<h4>Blood Puddle Pillow</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_5a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_5a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="672"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://technabob.com/blog/2008/10/30/blood-puddle-pillows-perfect-for-halloween-slumber/">Technabob</a> and <a href="http://dornob.com/creepy-inflatable-blood-pool-pillows-too-realistic/">Dornob</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Sometimes you\u2019re so dead tired you want to shout out, <em>\u201cDon\u2019t let anyone wake me unless it\u2019s the coroner!\u201d</em> Sleep on the Blood Puddle Pillow and your wish just might come true. Of course, choosing to have a massive brain hemorrhage while clowning around with the Blood Puddle Pillow just might be a self-fulfilling prophecy.</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_5b" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_5b.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="353"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(image via: <a href="http://www.gearfuse.com/blood-puddle-pillow-to-scare-your-loved-ones/">Gearfuse</a>)</span></p>\n<p>This is a rare example of a product that can be used by both Man and Man\u2019s Best Friend. We were going to call it the \u201cBlood Poodle Pillow\u201d but reading that would probably make your head explode for real.</p>\n<h4>Bloody Gloomy Bear Claw Pillows</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_6a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_6a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="432"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://sclick.net/new-gadgets-2/weird-gadgets-gloomy-bear-arm-pillows-strange-bizarre-odd-gadgets.html">Sclick</a>)</span></p>\n<p>So you think Japan is all Hello Kitty cuteness and giggly schoolgirls squealing <em>\u201ckawaii!\u201d</em> every 2 seconds? That pretty much covers it but admixed into the sea of smiley-faced sweetness is an undercurrent of unease. Take these <a href="http://blog.tboox.com/2010/08/gloomy-bear-arms/">Gloomy Bear Claw Pillows</a>, for instance.</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_6b" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_6b.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="567"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://blog.tboox.com/2010/08/gloomy-bear-arms/">TBOOX</a>)</span></p>\n<p>The story of the surprisingly popular Gloomy Bear character goes something like this: Gloomy Bear was orphaned as a cub and rescued by a young boy. As Gloomy grew, his natural wild &amp; savage instincts prompted him to attack his owner in increasingly violent ways \u2013 as the bloody red claws indicate. That\u2019s OK, though\u2026 he\u2019s pink!</p>\n<h4>Sleeping With The Fishes Pillow</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_7" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_7.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="468"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://nexus404.com/Blog/2007/04/09/bizarre-salmon-pillow/">TFTS</a>)</span></p>\n<p>We\u2019ve heard of slapping a chilly T-bone steak over a shiner but laying one\u2019s head upon a fresh salmon? Y\u2019know, it just might work\u2026 for WHAT, we don\u2019t know. Suffice to say that the Fresh Salmon Pillow is 70cm (28\u2033) long and according to the manufacturer, does not smell. So much for realism.</p>\n<h4>\u201dWith This Pillow, I Thee Wed\u201d</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_8a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_8a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="671"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://ringoblog.com/ring-by-type/casual-rings/pillow-ring-for-resting-your-head/">Ring-o-Blog</a> and <a href="http://www.designboom.com/snapshot/gallery.php?SNAPSHOT_ID=21&amp;GALLERY_ID=1022">DesignBoom</a>)</span></p>\n<p>You can wear your heart on your sleeve but can you wear your boredom on your finger? Yes, yes you can! The \u201c<a href="http://www.pilopilo.com/">Pilo-Pilo</a>\u201d mini cushion ring from designers Lenny Ming Lo and Sae Shigeto of <a href="http://www.downstairs-studio.com">Downstairs Studio</a> offers those bored at work, play or life in general an instant respite from tedium right at their fingertips (or thereabouts).</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_8b" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_8b.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="523"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://www.pilopilo.com/">Pilo-Pilo Shop</a> and <a href="http://www.designboom.com/snapshot/gallery.php?SNAPSHOT_ID=21&amp;GALLERY_ID=1022">DesignBoom</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Definition of \u201ckilling with kindness\u201d? Bring a fistful of Pilo-Pilo rings to a brass knuckle fight. You probably won\u2019t win but you\u2019ll definitely crack a few smiles.</p>\n<h4>Steel This Pillow</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_9" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_9.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="533"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://oilycog.com/pillow.htm">Oilycog</a>)</span></p>\n<p>So you\u2019re Bond, James Bond, and Oddjob\u2019s razor-sharp fedora just zipped by your nose. How to reply? Make like Tom Brady and toss one of these steely pillows his way. They only LOOK like they\u2019re encased in iron, however, so prepare to run like Ochocinco after an incriminating tweet once you\u2019ve let the fluffy faux-ferrous missile fly.</p>\n<h4>Sleeping Pill-O</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_10a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_10a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="479"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://artisticthings.com/sleep-away-the-pain/">Artistic Things</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Jean-Philippe and Gaston Valeur of <a href="http://artisticthings.com/sleep-away-the-pain/">CarteBlanche</a> are into \u201ccocaine-chic couture\u201d but their so-called \u201cPill-O\u201d references equally abusable but outwardly respectable prescription drugs.</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_10b" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_10b.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="400"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(image via: <a href="http://artisticthings.com/sleep-away-the-pain/">Artistic Things</a>)</span></p>\n<p>The Pill-O is an interesting concept to be sure but we\u2019re not convinced of its practicality in real life situations\u2026 say, going through the baggage check at the airport. Just tell those burly TSA dudes it\u2019s a pillow, they\u2019ll understand.</p>\n<h4>Giant Condom Pillow</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_11a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_11a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="565"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://pixelcurse.com/inspiration-2/extraordinary-pillow-design-ideas">PixelCurse</a> and <a href="http://www.etsy.com/listing/27157219/hand-silkscreened-giant-condom-pillow?ref=vl_other_1">ETSY / LittleElk</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Now here\u2019s an excellent example of thinking ahead. The Giant Condom Pillow not only serves as a friendly reminder to sleep (or whatever) safe, it features a handy-dandy pocket within which one may store miniature versions of the pillow conveniently within reach. The decorative lining adds to the professionally finished look &amp; feel of the pillow.</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_11b" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_11b.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="391"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(image via: <a href="http://www.etsy.com/listing/27157219/hand-silkscreened-giant-condom-pillow?ref=vl_other_1">ETSY / LittleElk</a>)</span></p>\n<p>So how is this frightening, you may ask\u2026 just put yourself in the place of some innocent yet nubile young ting returning to her first date\u2019s pad for, ahem, coffee. He gives her the grand tour and what do her wondering eyes see but his intentions, laid out plainly along with his PJs. Now THAT\u2019s scary!</p>\n<h4>\u201cThe Creepiest Pillow Ever\u201d</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_12a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_12a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="590"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://www.odditycentral.com/pics/the-creepiest-pillow-ever.html">Oddity Central</a>)</span></p>\n<p>To be honest, we wouldn\u2019t want to lay on this pillow with <em>somebody else\u2019s</em> head. How to describe this dark <a href="http://smastroni.blogspot.com/">work of occult folk art</a>? It looks a little like Chuckie, the malevolent &amp; murderous doll from the Child\u2019s Play horror flick franchise crossed with the Hypnotoad. It\u2019s a good thing Charles Lee Ray didn\u2019t transfer his evil soul into this pillow\u2026 let\u2019s just hope and keep on hoping!</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_12b" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_12b.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="413"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(image via: <a href="http://www.odditycentral.com/pics/the-creepiest-pillow-ever.html">Oddity Central</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Now was this really necessary? Wasn\u2019t <em>\u201cThe Creepiest Pillow Ever\u201d</em> more than creepy enough without posing it inside a box with only its soulless eyes showing?</p>\n<h4>Ernesto Neto\u2019s Bed Pillow</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_13" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_13.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="480"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(image via: <a href="http://www.core.form-ula.com/2010/07/19/core-curation-ernesto-neto/">Core.Form-Ula</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Brazilian artist <a href="http://mattresszine.com/mattress-news/crazy-vertical-bed-by-ernesto-neto/">Ernesto Neto</a> gets his inspiration from neo-concretism, an artistic movement of the late 1950s and early 1960s in which art is equated with living organisms to form a sort of \u201corganic architecture\u201d. We\u2019re not sure what Neto\u2019s gigantic pillow/bed is meant to represent but if used in a pillow-fight, it could be considered a WMD.</p>\n<h4>The Screaming Scream Pillow</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_14a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_14a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="605"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://www.etsy.com/listing/53328180/sale-cameo-pillow-cover-the-scream?ref=tre-4c7d789ba5948eefbc59ac29-12">Warning Label Creations</a> and <a href="http://www.kleargear.com/2058.html">KlearGear</a>)</span></p>\n<p>It had to have taken a deranged mind to come up with <a href="http://www.baronbob.com/unusual-pillows.htm">The Scream Pillow</a> but to add a mechanism that invites one to <em>\u201csqueeze me and I scream\u201d</em>? That\u2019s pure genius right there. Of course, once you unpack your pillow and lay it out on the bed, your better half won\u2019t know his or her pillow actually screams until their sleepy, unassuming head hits it\u2026 YouTube, here you come!</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_14" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_14.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="567"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(image via: <a href="http://overthenet.blogspot.com/2007/03/tickle-me-elmo.html">Over the Net and On the Table</a>)</span></p>\n<p>The Screaming Scream Pillow is an astonishing example of what happens when high art meets low novelty. Really, what\u2019s next? A Mona Lisa whoopee cushion? That could work, actually\u2026 now we\u2019ll finally know what that enigmatic smile\u2019s all about.</p>\n<h4>The Godfather Of All Pillows</h4>\n<p><img title="pillows_15a" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_15a.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="625"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(images via: <a href="http://www.kropserkel.com/horse_head_pillow.htm">Kropserkel</a> and <a href="http://lostangelesblog.wordpress.com/2009/04/10/godfather-horse-head-pillow-seriously/">Lost Angeles</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Induce the mother of all coronary infarctions with the <a href="http://www.kropserkel.com/horse_head_pillow.htm">godfather of all pillows</a>! This plush, life-sized and anatomically correct (for the most part) horse\u2019s head was inspired by the iconic scene in the film <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0068646/">The Godfather</a> when Mr Bigtime Hollywood Producer learns what happens when Don Corleone receives bad news. Whether on-screen or in real life, with this replica or an actual equine noggin, the end result will undoubtedly be the same.</p>\n<p><img title="pillows_15" src="http://img.weburbanist.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/pillows_15.jpg" alt="" width="468" height="428"><span style="font-size:xx-small">(image via: <a href="http://www.duvetandpillowwarehouse.co.uk/blog/2009/09/10-bizarre-pillows/">DAPW</a>)</span></p>\n<p>Now you can re-enact that classic bit of gory film lore in your very own home, starring your very own wife\u2026 pending her waking up half the neighborhood and filing for divorce. The <a href="http://inventorspot.com/relationship_advice">Horse Head Pillow</a> is available stuffed or unstuffed, the latter option intended to reduce shipping charges. Yep, you\u2019ll need every cent you\u2019ve got once she (or he \u2013 it\u2019s a unisex shocker) sics a \u201cmob\u201d of lawyers on you for being a real horse\u2019s rear.</p>\n\n\n\n          <div>\n          <hr style="clear:both" width="475px" align="left">\n          <h3>Want More? Click for Great Related Content on WebUrbanist:</h3>\n          <div style="clear:both">\n            <a href="http: