    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/8df8612857272b3e.html':'<img src="http://cdn.archinect.net/images/514x/97/972afd28f1b06d5e9c40b88e20c6bd82.jpg" width="514" height="354" border="0" title="" alt=""><em><p>The exhibition, curated by Elias Redstone, originated as an online project and showcases 60 architecture magazines, fanzines and journals from over 20 countries. From Australia and Argentina to the UK and USA, these independent publications are reframing how people relate to their built environment \u2013 taking comment and criticism out of just an architectural arena and into everyday life.</p></em><p>\n\tWe\'re honored to have both our new <a href="http://shop.archinect.com/product/ai-weiwei-zine" rel="nofollow">Archinect News Digest \'zine</a>, as well as <a href="http://shop.archinect.com/product/bracket-on-farming" rel="nofollow">Bracket</a>, included in the upcoming ARCHI-ZINES exhibition at the AA in London.</p>\n<p>\n\t<img alt="" src="http://cdn.archinect.net/uploads/qq/qqcikfsrair3sjrx.png"></p>', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/2e46025f32559860.html':'<img src="http://cdn.archinect.net/images/514x/02/02lba8lb2iix7pln.jpg" width="514" height="395" border="0" title="" alt=""><em><p>This week, MVRDV, The Why Factory and the JUT Foundation for Arts and Architecture opened the fourth edition of the exhibition series \u201cMuseum of Tomorrow\u201d in Taipei. Under the title \u201cThe Vertical Village\u201d the exhibition explores the rapid urban transformation in East Asia, the qualities of urban villages and the potential to realize this in a much denser, vertical way as a radical alternative to the identical block architecture with standard apartments and its consequences for the city.</p></em>\n', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/ba0398d6f1d6c08f.html':'<img src="http://cdn.archinect.net/images/514x/0d/0doglgdjmbe0yt9z.jpg" width="514" height="341" border="0" title="" alt=""><em><p>He was the ultimate perfectionist and demanded of himself as he demanded of others. We are better as individuals and certainly wiser as architects through the experience of the last two years and more of working for him. His participation was so intense and creative that our memory will be that of working with one of the truly great designers and mentors.</p></em>\n', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/49403ed57ca5b280.html':'<img src="http://cdn.archinect.net/images/514x/8v/8vkgojc7xr4ehsf3.jpg" width="514" height="209" border="0" title="" alt=""><em><p>\u201cHOW DOES IT FEEL TO BE FORTY YEARS TOO SOON?\u201d Question of the year from Jeffrey Kipnis to Glen Small at a rooftop bar.</p></em><p>\n\tAn exciting, substantial and honest review of <a href="http://www.smallatlarge.com/2011/09/sci-arc-screen-test-i-shall-return/#more-441" rel="nofollow">SCI Arc 2011 Thesis Reviews</a> from one of its founding fathers and great critic, Glen Howard Small.</p>', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/6f9886073fc6e956.html':'<img src="http://cdn.archinect.net/images/514x/n7/n7e0qxtyh9xe7v76.jpg" width="322" height="498" border="0" title="" alt=""><em><p>The architects recognize that the armory as an exhibition space is a far cry from conventional \u201cwhite cube\u201d galleries, or what Mr. Herzog called \u201cegocentric, architecturally driven museums.\u201d But he said the spaces are likely to inspire artists, not limit them. \u201cArtists have increasingly started to like strange places to put their art,\u201d he said. \u201cThe specific conditions are unique and interesting and every artist is challenged to put his paintings or performances in such historic conditions.\u201d</p></em>\n', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/6dd9ec3b743e81a5.html':'<img src="http://cdn.archinect.net/images/514x/f1/f165uf2ffdf5ycgi.jpg" width="514" height="357" border="0" title="" alt=""><em><p>"Migration has always been the vital essence of Mediterranean cities. New cultures have continued to be included in daily life, and they have fertilised and expressed themselves through complex urban forms with richness and imagination." - Giancarlo De Carlo</p></em><p>\n\tLaunched by DOMUS Magazine and followed by a Joseph Grima op-ed addressed to \xa0Mr. Herman Van Rompuy,\xa0President of the European Council,\xa0calling for an urgenct immigration affairs action between the two old continents with different scales of contradictions and compliments. DOMUS Project Heracles continues to publish its postcard entries from worldwide entrants. They all represent important and inclusive body of ideas, commentaries and rich visual materials, selected by invited jury members proposing a Eurafrican infrastructural bridge connecting the two continents over Gibraltar.</p>\n<p>\n\tIt is the wealth of ideas, hits and misses, obliviousness,\xa0skillful\xa0image making and deeper conflicts addressed in this virtual exhibition in installments. There are 8 sections so far, including one entry by <a href="http://put.edidomus.it/domus/binaries/imagedata/big_358053_9680_Foto%2047%20fronte-retro_UPD1.jpg" rel="nofollow">yours truly</a>\xa0on section #6...</p>', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/64afec8c16c92cb0.html':'<img src="http://cdn.archinect.net/images/514x/a9/a93f3064b2b60e7414d3915ab82c614a.jpg" width="190" height="317" border="0" title="" alt=""><em><p>Mr. Gehry predicted the panel will benefit from Justice Breyer\u2019s sense of calm. \u201cPeople have biases,\u201d he said. \u201cAnd having a guy like that, who is used to that kind of negotiation and discussion, could be very interesting. He\u2019s a real straight shooter.\u201d\n\nJustice Breyer said he hopes to advocate for high-quality design in government buildings.</p></em>\n', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/90653b991f004851.html':'<img src="http://cdn.archinect.net/images/514x/0c/0cx9brksmx3rpzmt.jpg" width="514" height="448" border="0" title="" alt=""><em><p>Given his stature, the demolition of Terminal 6 arguably ranks as the most significant loss of a transportation building in New York since Pennsylvania Station was razed in the early 1960s.\n\nMr. Cobb does not think of the two events as analogous, however. \u201cThis is not pure greed,\u201d he said. \u201cThis is the myopic view of engineers. They just can\u2019t figure out how to reuse it and they don\u2019t put enough value on it to figure out how to reuse it.\u201d</p></em>\n', 
