    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/7f80afedef90beb3.html':'<p></p><p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/postmodern5.jpg"><img title="Fahrenheit 451 bungalow" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/postmodern5.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="438"></a></p>\n<p>I\u2019ve always admired that British pluck when it comes to marketing \u2013 from what I\u2019ve witnessed the English have a masterful way of cranking everything up a notch if they want to get your attention.\xa0 So naturally, when one of the country\u2019s graphic design and marketing firms wanted to sell their building they made their marketing materials quite compelling.\xa0 Named <a href="http://www.bungalowindustries.com/index.html">Bungalow Industries</a>, the firm pulled out all the stops moving their remarkable real estate.\xa0 Here\u2019s a look at some of the interior photos (which look like they sprung from the pages of Dwell).</p>\n<p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/postmodern4.jpg"><img title="Fahrenheit 451 bungalow" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/postmodern4.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="617"></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/postmodern1.jpg"><img title="Fahrenheit 451 bungalow" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/postmodern1.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="687"></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/postmodern2.jpg"><img title="Fahrenheit 451 bungalow" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/postmodern2.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="605"></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/postmodern3.jpg"><img title="Fahrenheit 451 bungalow" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/postmodern3.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="557"></a></p>\n<p>And here is the brochure they created for it \u2013 sells the house and their design services too (you might say).\xa0 Included are the original ads for the Edgcumbe Park development \u2013 and a variety of stills from the film Fahrenheit 451, starring Julie Christie, which was shot in the neighborhood in the 1960\u2032s.</p>\n<div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=8M0_K08-ZVw:QIk3C1fJi50:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=8M0_K08-ZVw:QIk3C1fJi50:7Q72WNTAKBA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=7Q72WNTAKBA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=8M0_K08-ZVw:QIk3C1fJi50:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=8M0_K08-ZVw:QIk3C1fJi50:l6gmwiTKsz0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=l6gmwiTKsz0" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=8M0_K08-ZVw:QIk3C1fJi50:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?i=8M0_K08-ZVw:QIk3C1fJi50:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=8M0_K08-ZVw:QIk3C1fJi50:TzevzKxY174"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=TzevzKxY174" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/BloomaciousDigs/~4/8M0_K08-ZVw" height="1" width="1">', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/ae8c79ffc36b6d42.html':'<p></p><p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun6.jpg"><img title="commuun paris fashionweek" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun6.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="600"></a></p>\n<p>Paris Fashion Week is under way which means loads of dramatic style, and styling.</p>\n<p>Commuun\u2019s Spring Summer 2012 show on Tuesday featured a collection of flowing, unstructured dresses, jackets, short pants that look very wearable.\xa0 I love the color blocking that gives the collection a contemporary feel.</p>\n<p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun7.jpg"><img title="commuun paris fashionweek" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun7.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="600"></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun4.jpg"><img title="commuun paris fashionweek" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun4.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="600"></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun2.jpg"><img title="commuun paris fashionweek" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun2.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="600"></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun1.jpg"><img title="commuun paris fashionweek" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun1.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="600"></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun5.jpg"><img title="commuun paris fashionweek" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun5.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="600"></a></p>\n<p>What do you think of the makeup from the show?\xa0 the delicate feather of white could be really fun in real life on the right gal in the right setting.</p>\n<p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun3.jpg"><img title="commuun paris fashionweek" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/commun3.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="600"></a></p>\n<div>\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=RUd5vTnePA4:GG_-OQq26f8:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=RUd5vTnePA4:GG_-OQq26f8:7Q72WNTAKBA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=7Q72WNTAKBA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=RUd5vTnePA4:GG_-OQq26f8:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=RUd5vTnePA4:GG_-OQq26f8:l6gmwiTKsz0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=l6gmwiTKsz0" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=RUd5vTnePA4:GG_-OQq26f8:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?i=RUd5vTnePA4:GG_-OQq26f8:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=RUd5vTnePA4:GG_-OQq26f8:TzevzKxY174"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=TzevzKxY174" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/BloomaciousDigs/~4/RUd5vTnePA4" height="1" width="1">', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/b65ea3961e5dd022.html':'<p></p><p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/tomato-salad.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="stacked tomato salad" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/tomato-salad.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="500"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:left">You and I know that anyone can slice up a tomato and some mozzarella cheese and place the pieces on a plate in the shape of a fan, tear up some bits of fresh basil, drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\xa0 But how many of you can cube and stack the same like this?\xa0 (I\u2019ll bet you can \u2013 and the kids will love it!)\xa0\xa0 9 cubes in a square on the bottom (staggered of course), 3 layers high.\xa0 Drizzle between layers with oil and season with a touch of salt for max flavor.\xa0 Whoa!\xa0 Enjoy.</p>\n<p align="left"><a href="http://twitter.com/home/?status=@bloomacious+Serving+Suggestion%3A+Stack+Your+Salad+Like+a+Rubik%E2%80%99s+Cube+http://leberpr.com/blog/?p=1991" title="Post to Twitter"><img src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/tweet-this/icons/tt-twitter-big2.png" alt="Post to Twitter"></a></p><div style="height:40px"></div><div>\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=TRJ5kpqtfxA:GBPAXjEU-Vc:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=TRJ5kpqtfxA:GBPAXjEU-Vc:7Q72WNTAKBA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=7Q72WNTAKBA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=TRJ5kpqtfxA:GBPAXjEU-Vc:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=TRJ5kpqtfxA:GBPAXjEU-Vc:l6gmwiTKsz0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=l6gmwiTKsz0" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=TRJ5kpqtfxA:GBPAXjEU-Vc:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?i=TRJ5kpqtfxA:GBPAXjEU-Vc:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=TRJ5kpqtfxA:GBPAXjEU-Vc:TzevzKxY174"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=TzevzKxY174" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/BloomaciousDigs/~4/TRJ5kpqtfxA" height="1" width="1">', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/663168609b61118a.html':'<p></p><p style="text-align:left"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/emb2.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="daniel kornrumpf" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/emb2.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="382"><br>\n</a>I was raised with two sisters who are very crafty \u2013 particularly with knitting, sewing and embroidery.</p>\n<p style="text-align:left">When I was growing up our walls were filled with frame after frame of needlepoint houses, embroidered kitties, and cross-stitched owls. I completed my fair share of those kits they sell at craft stores too, but to be honest somewhere along the way my affection for this art form has diminished.</p>\n<p style="text-align:left">With the rising popularity of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suzani">Suzani</a>, the concept of needlework has become much more acceptable.\xa0 But textiles are quite different than embroidered and framed farm houses any way you look at it.\xa0\xa0 But thanks to the creativity of several artists, I would say embroidery may well be finding its way back into the hip-cycle.</p>\n<p style="text-align:left">Above, and below, artist <a href="http://danielkornrumpf.com/home.html">Daniel Kornrumpf</a> is making a name for himself embroidering portraits people have posted on Facebook, Twitter and Flickr.\xa0 I love the impressionist spin he takes on these.</p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/embroider1.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="daniel kornrumpf" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/embroider1.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="514"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:left">Yes, you\u2019ve probably seen this collection of needlepoint pillows <a href="http://www.jonathanadler.com/Needlepoint-pillows/">Jonathan Adler</a> has reintroduced into the American lexicon of decorating. If anyone else tried this I doubt they\u2019d get very far, but in JA\u2019s decidedly cool hands they work!</p>\n<p style="text-align:left"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/JA1.jpg"><img title="jonathan adler" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/JA1.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="660"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:left">These last three pieces are by <a href="http://www.etsy.com/shop/Moxiedoll?ref=pr_shop_more">etsy artist MoxieDoll</a> and I love the fun graphic feel these offer.\xa0 Sold in their hoops I would love to see these grouped like plates on a wall.</p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/il_fullxfull.238415397.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="moxiedoll embroidery" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/il_fullxfull.238415397.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="495"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/il_fullxfull.207801203.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="embroidery" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/il_fullxfull.207801203.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="530"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/il_fullxfull.146333619.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="embroidery" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/il_fullxfull.146333619.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="515"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:left">\n<p align="left"><a href="http://twitter.com/home/?status=@bloomacious+Is+Embroidery+Hip+%28again%29%3F+http://leberpr.com/blog/?p=1983" title="Post to Twitter"><img src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/tweet-this/icons/tt-twitter-big2.png" alt="Post to Twitter"></a></p><div style="height:40px"></div><div>\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=vhfSq6g7Cpw:GlbiTchR36Y:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=vhfSq6g7Cpw:GlbiTchR36Y:7Q72WNTAKBA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=7Q72WNTAKBA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=vhfSq6g7Cpw:GlbiTchR36Y:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=vhfSq6g7Cpw:GlbiTchR36Y:l6gmwiTKsz0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=l6gmwiTKsz0" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=vhfSq6g7Cpw:GlbiTchR36Y:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?i=vhfSq6g7Cpw:GlbiTchR36Y:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=vhfSq6g7Cpw:GlbiTchR36Y:TzevzKxY174"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=TzevzKxY174" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/BloomaciousDigs/~4/vhfSq6g7Cpw" height="1" width="1"></p>', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/a4c3c51e4775d72a.html':'<p></p><p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/img-frances-palmer-plates_135900399303.jpg_article_singleimage.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="frances palmer ceramics" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/img-frances-palmer-plates_135900399303.jpg_article_singleimage.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="450"></a></p>\n<p>I was really dazzled this month when I picked up the September issue of <a href="http://www.cottages-gardens.com/">Connecticut Cottages and Gardens</a>. On the cover is a remarkable collection of vases and pots created by local potter Frances Palmer. In another life I want to come back as Frances, ginormous dahlia garden and all.\xa0 {<a href="http://francespalmerpottery.com/CTCG-0911.pdf">See the tear sheets here</a>}</p>\n<p>I would love to have the time, talent and patience to create these earthy, elegant and compelling pieces.\xa0 For now I will merely enjoy the photos (<a href="http://francespalmerpottery.com/FP_pearl.htm">and buy them</a>).\xa0 Here\u2019s a look at a few of my favorites.</p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Frances-Palmer-3.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Frances Palmer Ceramics" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Frances-Palmer-3.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="750"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/FP.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Frances Palmer Ceramics" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/FP.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="359"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/0a9b7ae939e43995ace65637f3f4b7de.jpeg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Frances Palmer Ceramics" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/0a9b7ae939e43995ace65637f3f4b7de.jpeg" alt="" width="500" height="351"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/5650106252_f18f56431a_b.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Frances Palmer Ceramics" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/5650106252_f18f56431a_b.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/5650185690_920a954442_b.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Frances Palmer Ceramics" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/5650185690_920a954442_b.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/vade.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Frances Palmer Ceramics" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/vade.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="450"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center">images from {<a href="http://www.vogue.com/vogue-daily/article/need-it-now-frances-palmers-floral-plates/">vogue</a>} {<a href="http://www.designsponge.com/2011/01/whats-in-your-toolbox-frances-palmer-2.html">design sponge</a>} {<a href="http://emersonmerrick.blogspot.com/search?q=frances+palmer">apple a day</a>} {<a href="http://stylebeat.blogspot.com/2011/05/swoon-worthy-lenox-hill-tablesettings.html">stylebeat</a>} {<a href="http://francespalmerpottery.com/index.htm">Frances Palmer</a>}</p>\n<p align="left"><a href="http://twitter.com/home/?status=@bloomacious+Drooling+Over+Frances+Palmer%E2%80%99s+Ceramics+http://leberpr.com/blog/?p=1971" title="Post to Twitter"><img src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/tweet-this/icons/tt-twitter-big2.png" alt="Post to Twitter"></a></p><div style="height:40px"></div><div>\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=cj1HA7Zh7Nc:lLdM6qa80GY:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=cj1HA7Zh7Nc:lLdM6qa80GY:7Q72WNTAKBA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=7Q72WNTAKBA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=cj1HA7Zh7Nc:lLdM6qa80GY:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=cj1HA7Zh7Nc:lLdM6qa80GY:l6gmwiTKsz0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=l6gmwiTKsz0" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=cj1HA7Zh7Nc:lLdM6qa80GY:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?i=cj1HA7Zh7Nc:lLdM6qa80GY:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=cj1HA7Zh7Nc:lLdM6qa80GY:TzevzKxY174"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=TzevzKxY174" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/BloomaciousDigs/~4/cj1HA7Zh7Nc" height="1" width="1">', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/041ecb72d938f6fd.html':'<p></p><p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/124984044CarolynLeber9152011101500AM.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="the blonds spring 2012" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/124984044CarolynLeber9152011101500AM.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="600"></a></p>\n<p>I always get a kick out of <strong>The Blonds</strong> ~ and their collection for this week\u2019s NYFW does not disappoint.\xa0 Katy Perry owes many of her zany outfits to the designing duo.\xa0\xa0 Maybe we\u2019ll see bits of this collection (obviously co-branded and sponsored by Playboy) on the controversial \u201c<a href="http://www.nbc.com/the-playboy-club/">Playboy Club</a>\u201d premiering on Monday on NBC.\xa0 The collection is play*ful*, and pieces would be fabulous on Beyonce, Gaga, Britney and any number of fabulous entertainers.\xa0 Here\u2019s a look:</p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/124984040CarolynLeber9152011101446AM.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="the blonds spring 2012" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/124984040CarolynLeber9152011101446AM.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="600"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/124984046CarolynLeber9152011101505AM.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="the blonds spring 2012" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/124984046CarolynLeber9152011101505AM.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="600"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/124984063CarolynLeber9152011101619AM.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="the blonds spring 2012" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/124984063CarolynLeber9152011101619AM.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="600"></a>