href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=ZSho1X4lcXY:yX9ucnA2YMM:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=ZSho1X4lcXY:yX9ucnA2YMM:l6gmwiTKsz0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=l6gmwiTKsz0" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=ZSho1X4lcXY:yX9ucnA2YMM:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?i=ZSho1X4lcXY:yX9ucnA2YMM:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=ZSho1X4lcXY:yX9ucnA2YMM:TzevzKxY174"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=TzevzKxY174" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/BloomaciousDigs/~4/ZSho1X4lcXY" height="1" width="1">', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/ddcc06e01cde7267.html':'<p></p><p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/fall-jumping.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="jumping for joy " src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/fall-jumping.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="663"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:left">It was gone, blown away in a hurricane, but with the help of line crews from all over North America our power is back!!\xa0 Thanks to the IPL, Duke Energy, (and one other company with green trucks that I can\u2019t remember the name of) crews from Indiana that moved into our area in Connecticut last week like an army and attacked the tangled lines, the downed trees, and made sense of our chaos.\xa0 We\u2019re so happy and relieved we literally jumped for joy on Saturday when our office buzzed back to life.</p>\n<p style="text-align:left">It seems as though when we ended the week on August 26th it was Summer, but after a strange week of toting office equipment to hotels and setting up laptops in coffee shops to keep progress flowing, it\u2019s turned into Fall.\xa0 Well yay to that!! Good to be back.</p>\n<p align="left"><a href="http://twitter.com/home/?status=@bloomacious+Not+That+We+Were+Gone%2C+But+Now+We%E2%80%99re+Back%21+http://leberpr.com/blog/?p=1928" title="Post to Twitter"><img src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/tweet-this/icons/tt-twitter-big2.png" alt="Post to Twitter"></a></p><div style="height:40px"></div><div>\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=el-Og1gMhhc:3_ExHhGpvVc:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=el-Og1gMhhc:3_ExHhGpvVc:7Q72WNTAKBA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=7Q72WNTAKBA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=el-Og1gMhhc:3_ExHhGpvVc:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=el-Og1gMhhc:3_ExHhGpvVc:l6gmwiTKsz0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=l6gmwiTKsz0" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=el-Og1gMhhc:3_ExHhGpvVc:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?i=el-Og1gMhhc:3_ExHhGpvVc:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=el-Og1gMhhc:3_ExHhGpvVc:TzevzKxY174"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=TzevzKxY174" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/BloomaciousDigs/~4/el-Og1gMhhc" height="1" width="1">', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/7b32d8b5986e0796.html':'<p></p><p><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/waiting.jpg"><img title="waiting" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/waiting.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="744"></a></p>\n<p>Last Sunday, early in the morning, Hurricane Irene came blasting through Connecticut.\xa0 While it was officially downgraded to a Tropical Storm, it\u2019s impact was quite strong.\xa0 Most notably for us, trees came down everywhere.\xa0 The power went out as was expected.\xa0 What was not expected was Connecticut Light &amp; Power\u2019s sluggish response to the storm.\xa0 After 5 days, we have yet to see a work crew anywhere in the vicinity of our town.\xa0 It\u2019s important to note, hundreds of AT&amp;T trucks have been on hand as well as Comcast, road and tree crews, street sweepers and town officials.</p>\n<p>Electric lines lay on the ground as cars drive over them, and hundreds of thousands of us have no running water (wells require electricity), lights, computers, printers, ect.\xa0 It feels like an episode from a movie, set in the 40\u2032s.</p>\n<p>We have relocated our offices to a town inland that has all the things an office needs to keep running, but the continued lack of power my patience on the ropes.\xa0 Will update you with more soon.</p>\n<p align="left"><a href="http://twitter.com/home/?status=@bloomacious+After+Five+Days+We%E2%80%99re+Still+Waiting+in+the+Dark+http://leberpr.com/blog/?p=1923" title="Post to Twitter"><img src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/tweet-this/icons/tt-twitter-big2.png" alt="Post to Twitter"></a></p><div style="height:40px"></div><div>\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=6vDeKnc_HHc:_PbsWPe99EE:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=6vDeKnc_HHc:_PbsWPe99EE:7Q72WNTAKBA"><img src="http://