    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/c0dde96498fd413a.html':'<p></p><p style="text-align:left"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-11.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="treasure and bond interior" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-11.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="375"></a><a href="http://shop.nordstrom.com/">Nordstrom\u2019s</a> charity shop \u201cTreasure &amp; Bond\u201d is scheduled to open today in NYC \u2013 don\u2019t confuse the concept with a Salvation Army \u2013 the goods they\u2019re selling are brand new and very hip \u2013 and not at all offered at a discount.\xa0 But 100% of the profits are going to help local New York groups and that\u2019s fabulous.</p>\n<p style="text-align:left">T&amp;B will benefit two charities each quarter; the current beneficiaries are the <a href="http://www.nypl.org/help/getting-oriented/resources-teens">New York Public Library\u2019s Programs for Children and Young Adults</a>, and <a href="http://www.nyc.gov/portal/site/nycgov/menuitem.c0935b9a57bb4ef3daf2f1c701c789a0/index.jsp?pageID=mayor_press_release&amp;catID=1194&amp;doc_name=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Fhtml%2Fom%2Fhtml%2F2011b%2Fpr282-11.html&amp;cc=unused1978&amp;rc=1194&amp;ndi=1">NYC\u2019s Young Men\u2019s Initiative.</a></p>\n<p style="text-align:left"><a href="http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2011/08/inside_nordstroms_do-gooder_co.html#">According to The Cut</a>, \u201cThe store credits the nonprofit business plan to Anna Wintour herself; apparently, the idea started with a phone call from the <em>Vogue</em> EIC to Pete Nordstrom.\u201d\xa0\xa0 Good thinking Ms. Wintour!!</p>\n<p style="text-align:left">The two-story, 11,137-square-foot store stocks is located at 350 West Broadway in Manhattan.\xa0 It will carry a wide range of goods including clothing and accessories for ladies and men on the 2nd floor.\xa0 The first floor is chock full of tabletop designs, home accessories and books.</p>\n<p style="text-align:left">So, tip of the hat to you Nordstrom for stepping up today.\xa0 We hope Treasure and Bond is a huge success and leads to similar stores in cities around the country!</p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-13.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Treasure and Bond, NYC" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-13.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="375"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-12.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Treasure and Bond, NYC" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-12.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="375"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-09.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Treasure and Bond, NYC" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-09.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="375"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-08.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Treasure and Bond, NYC" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-08.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="375"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/16NORDSTROM-articleLarge.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Treasure and Bond, NYC" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/16NORDSTROM-articleLarge.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="288"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:left"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-02.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Treasure and Bond, NYC" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/treasureandbond-02.jpg"