/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?i=-lw1C1dOKeg:dtpngcvf8pw:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?a=-lw1C1dOKeg:dtpngcvf8pw:TzevzKxY174"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/BloomaciousDigs?d=TzevzKxY174" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/BloomaciousDigs/~4/-lw1C1dOKeg" height="1" width="1">', 
    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/fefc708411762122.html':'<p></p><p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM11.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="kirsty mitchell photography" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM11.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="335"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:left">Have a creative desert facing you?\xa0 Not to worry, UK based photographer Kirsty Mitchell would like to inspire and thrill you with her remarkable Wonderland Series of images.</p>\n<p style="text-align:left">I can\u2019t help but see a few Gagaisms in this collection (perhaps I\u2019ve been <del>scarred</del> jaded by that meat dress).\xa0 But in truth Mitchell is a bit more careful in her costuming and rather than folly, her settings seem to make a lot of artistic sense.\xa0 Wonderland is meant to be an unexplained collection of strange and magical characters, set in woodlands and pastures \u2013 an homage to Mitchell\u2019s mother who passed away in 2008, shortly before the inception of this series.</p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM12.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell&#39;s Wonderland Series" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM12.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="335"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM21.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell&#39;s Wonderland Series" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM21.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="332"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:left">I\u2019m not going to pretend that Hume\u2019s use of vivid color against somewhat monochromatic backdrops doesn\u2019t grab me and shake me up a bit \u2013 but I\u2019m also enthralled with the sheer fun captured in each frame.\xa0 I have a feeling that this collection started as a lark and became an obsession.\xa0 As Hume explains it:</p>\n<p style="text-align:left"><em>Originally it had began as a much smaller concept, in the form of just a few shoots that would span the summer, but nothing prepared us for the emotional journey it became, and the very special friendships it produced\u2026.We had no budget, and relied on the kindness of people donating their unwanted treasures, and anything we could scavenge to customise. The landscape became my main focus, researching areas of natural beauty, unique pockets of flowers that bloom for only a few weeks a year, and shooting these at their most ethereal times of day. </em></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM20.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM20.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="404"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM19.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM19.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="519"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM18.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM18.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="332"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM5.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM5.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM6.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM6.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="496"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM31.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="kirsty mitchell photography" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM31.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="330"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM7.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM7.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="439"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM8.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM8.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="432"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM9.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM9.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="499"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM4.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM4.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="353"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM13.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="Kristy Mitchell" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM13.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="481"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM151.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" title="kirsty mitchell photography" src="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM151.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="503"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center"><a href="http://leberpr.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/KM22.jpg"><img style="border:1px solid black" t