    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/974d1358efa9e92c.html':'<p><a href="http://fashionista.com/2011/10/steve-jobs-preferred-turtleneck-brand-st-croix-reports-nearly-100-increase-in-sales/"><img src="http://fashionista.com/uploads/2011/10/Picture-6-150x115.png" style="float:left;margin:0 15px 15px 0"></a><p>A rep from Men\u2019s luxury brand St. Croix apparently told TMZ today that their turtleneck sales have shot up dramatically since yesterday\u2019s untimely death of Apple genius <a href="http://fashionista.com/2011/10/quote-of-the-day-steve-jobs-on-death-and-making-big-choices/">Steve Jobs</a> (The brand\u2019s black turtlenecks were a part of his <a href="http://fashionista.com/2011/08/steve-jobs-resigns-as-ceo-of-apple-a-tribute-to-his-uniform/">uniform</a>). From <a href="http://www.tmz.com/2011/10/06/steve-jobs-mock-turtleneck-sales-st-croix-knitwear-apple-ceo-keynote-speech-address-sweater/#.To3px5yCLdA">TMZ</a>:</p>\n<blockquote><p>You\u2019ll recall, Jobs famously rocked the high-neck knitwear during his keynote addresses for Apple \u2014 and now, the company that makes his favorite sweaters says Jobs\u2019 death has doubled its business.</p>\n<p>A rep for the St. Croix clothing brand tells TMZ, as soon as news broke that Jobs had passed, their mock turtlenecks flew off the shelves \u2014 adding, St. Croix has experienced an \u201calmost 100% increase in sales\u201d since yesterday.</p></blockquote>\n<p><strong><a href="http://fashionista.com/2011/10/steve-jobs-preferred-turtleneck-brand-st-croix-reports-nearly-100-increase-in-sales/">Continue reading \xbb</a></strong></p><hr style="clear:both"><h3 style="text-align:center"><em>Follow Fashionista on <a href="http://twitter.com/Fashionista_com">Twitter</a> or become a fan on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/Fashionistacom/93829151519">Facebook</a>.</em></h3><hr><p><iframe src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~ah/f/ltrk2f94jsu2vikemgiavpcm94/300/250?ca=1&amp;fh=280#http%3A%2F%2Ffashionista.com%