    'tag%3Agoogle.com%2C2005%3Areader/item/c1e76dc16dfc2f0b.html':'<img alt="congress-climate-action-clear.jpg" src="http://www.treehugger.com/congress-climate-action-clear.jpg" width="468" height="312">\n<em>Photo credit: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/abir82/">Abeeeer</a> via <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/abir82/4048700421/sizes/m/in/set-72157622672691662/">Flickr</a>/<a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/">CC BY </a></em>\n\nThe policies that Congressmen and women adhere to in their everyday lives occasionally act as a useful reflection of the political trends pulling at the nation in general. Consider earlier this year, when invigorated, Tea Party-backed Republicans <a href="http://www.treehugger.com/files/2011/02/gop-cancels-biodegradable-packaging-styrofoam.php">did away with the biodegradab...<a href="http://www.treehugger.com/files/2011/10/us_congress_turn_90_percent_trash_energy.php?campaign=th_rss">Read the full story on TreeHugger</a><br>\t<a href="http://api.tweetmeme.com/share?url=http://www.treehugger.com/files/2011/10/us_congress_turn_90_percent_trash_energy.php&amp;service=bit.ly"><img src="http://api.tweetmeme.com/imagebutton.gif?url=http://www.treehugger.com/files/2011/10/us_congress_turn_90_percent_trash_energy.php" height="61" width="51"></a><a href="javascript:void(0);"><img src="http://www.treehugger.com/images/rss-fb-share.gif" height="61" width="70"></a><div>\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/treehuggersite?a=7J6LxYy--vI:sBcHAjeSIPA:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/treehuggersite?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/treehuggersite?a=7J6LxYy--vI:sBcHAjeSIPA:2mJPEYqXBVI"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/treehuggersite?d=2mJPEYqXBVI" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/treehuggersite?a=7J6LxYy--vI:sBcHAjeSIPA:DLYy-l-dIDg"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/treehuggersite?d=DLYy-l-dIDg" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src